  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "While most models only consider spectral information for graph construction, DGU-HSI introduces a dual GCN that simultaneously extracts spatial and spectral features.In [30], a multi-branch deep learning framework is introduced for land scene classification, addressing challenges such as complex textures, cluttered backgrounds, small object sizes, and scale variations.",
    "The proposed framework efficiently integrates global contextual features and multi-scale features through two branches, where the first extracts global contextual information, and the second employs a fully convolutional network (FCN) for multi-scale local feature extraction.",
    "These methods demonstrate good classification performance over existing CNN-based state-of-the-art methods, but the computational complexity and model complexity are still challenges that need to be overcome.In recent years, a slew of studies based on attention mechanisms have developed in the field of remote sensing image classification.",
    "Authors in [31] proposed a fuzzy classification approach using a multi-scale strategy to extract visual attention features of high-resolution remote sensing images.",
    "To enhance the classification performance, authors in [32] construct a recurring attention model which deceptively picks certain crucial regions in images while discarding some non-critical information."
  ],
